pageContext.claim: “When I was at the wall the other day, Border Patrol said they have 150 people they caught that day who weren't from Mexico. I said, "That's a strange statement." They said, "No, these are the people that weren't from Mexico." And I was surprised. Three were from Pakistan. Four were from another Mid-East -- two Mid-East countries. And many of them were from other countries, including China -- countries all over the world. A hundred and fifty of the people, as he said, were not from Mexico. Now, they caught many, many more, but that's a 150 people coming from companies that -- you know, really, countries that you wouldn't believe.”
pageContext.analysis: This is what the briefer told Trump on Jan. 10: "Just yesterday, we apprehended 133 people from countries other than Central America and Mexico. That includes individuals from India, Pakistan, China, Romania, Ecuador, Nicaragua, on and on and on." There was no mention of anyone from a Middle Eastern country.
